Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling and predicting popularity of online content, which is related to social networks and information dissemination. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the development of a novel mathematical model for predicting popularity. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper focuses on analyzing popularity of videos on YouTube. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with predicting popularity of online content based on external promotions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of a mathematical model to analyze and predict popularity of online content.
